Ask HN: How widespread are custom/bespoke dtabase systems?
text: Are companies writing custom database systems from scratches (I mean "starting from zero" and designing+implementing systems that fit specific needs and employ data models that are more tightly tied to characteristics of data sets and interactions with these data) to tailor needs better suited to certain clients just a tiny niche tied to few companies or is it an actual booming "invisible market" lurking in shadows of obscurity that is not that much talked about "in the mainstream"? I can certainly see them being created for social media platforms or search engines. How about world outside of these two groups? Are existing popular "mainstream" database solutions enough in the "real work" or they are areas when need for more closely tailored solutions are blatantly obvious?

title: Comparison TorchScript model vs. ONNX format for Speed inference in C++
text:
What do you think about the comparison of the title?

I was completing a course where one of the topics was deployment and an inference model was created that used the to_torchscript model.

Until now I thought ONNX was the way to go.

This is my impression so far:

Setup: It might be a bit more difficult for ONNX as you have to write the model translation code from PyTorch to ONNX and the inference code (I might be wrong about this, please comment)

Speed: ??? This is what interests me the most

My goal is to use the model stored in Python and load and inference model in the language of C Plus Plus and?
